div.p:
The Recollections of this Nature, and Recantations of former Principles, together with the strange Horror and Consternation those we are speaking of lye under at particular times, is decypher'd by Juvenal in these Lines;




                           Satyr 13.Hi sunt qui trepidant & ad omnia fulgura Pallent

Cum tonat Exanimes primo quoque murmure Coeli.
